cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the prediction of sentiment and emotions in visual content, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of classifiers to predict adjectives and nouns suggests a machine learning approach, which is also relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the study of contributions of adjective and noun components could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of understanding how users search for and interpret visual content.
